{"PubmedArticle": [{"MedlineCitation": {"SpaceFlightMission": [], "OtherID": [], "InvestigatorList": [], "OtherAbstract": [], "CitationSubset": ["IM"], "KeywordList": [], "GeneralNote": [], "PMID": "19479260", "DateCompleted": {"Year": "2009", "Month": "07", "Day": "21"}, "DateRevised": {"Year": "2021", "Month": "10", "Day": "20"}, "Article": {"ArticleDate": [{"Year": "2009", "Month": "05", "Day": "29"}], "Language": ["eng"], "ELocationID": ["10.1007/s00299-009-0712-4"], "Journal": {"ISSN": "1432-203X", "JournalIssue": {"Volume": "28", "Issue": "7", "PubDate": {"Year": "2009", "Month": "Jul"}}, "Title": "Plant cell reports", "ISOAbbreviation": "Plant Cell Rep"}, "ArticleTitle": "Production and cytogenetic characterization of intertribal somatic hybrids between Brassica napus and Isatis indigotica and backcross progenies.", "Pagination": {"StartPage": "1105", "EndPage": "1113", "MedlinePgn": "1105-13"}, "Abstract": {"AbstractText": ["Intertribal somatic hybrids between Brassica napus (2n = 38, AACC) and a dye and medicinal plant Isatis indigotica (2n = 14, II) were obtained by fusions of mesophyll protoplasts. From a total of 237 calli, only one symmetric hybrid (S2) and five asymmetric hybrids (As1, As4, As6, As7 and As12) were established in the field. These hybrids showed some morphological variations and had very low pollen fertility. Hybrids S2 and As1 possessed 2n = 52 (AACCII), the sum of the parental chromosomes, and As12 had 2n = 66 (possibly AACCIIII). Hybrids As4, As6 and As7 were mixoploids (2n = 48-62). Genomic in situ hybridization analysis revealed that pollen mother cells at diakinesis of As1 contained 26 bivalents comprising 19 from B. napus and 7 from I. indigotica and mainly showed the segregation 26:26 at anaphase I (AI) with 7 I. indigotica chromosomes in each polar group. Four BC(1) plants from As1 after pollinated by B. napus resembled mainly B. napus in morphology but also exhibited some characteristics from I. indigotica. These plants produced some seeds on selfing or pollination by B. napus. They had 2n = 45 (AACCI) and underwent pairing among the I. indigotica chromosomes and/or between the chromosomes of two parents at diakinesis. All hybrids mainly had the AFLP banding patterns from the addition of two parents plus some alterations. B. napus contributed chloroplast genomes in majority of the hybrids but some also had from I. indigotica. Production of B. napus-I. indigotica additions would be of considerable importance for genome analysis and breeding."]}, "AuthorList": [{"AffiliationInfo": [{"Identifier": [], "Affiliation": "College of Life Science, Hubei University, 430062, Wuhan, People's Republic of China."}], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Du", "ForeName": "Xue-zhu", "Initials": "XZ"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Ge", "ForeName": "Xian-hong", "Initials": "XH"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Yao", "ForeName": "Xing-cheng", "Initials": "XC"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Zhao", "ForeName": "Zhi-gang", "Initials": "ZG"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Li", "ForeName": "Zai-yun", "Initials": "ZY"}], "PublicationTypeList": ["Journal Article", "Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't"]}, "MedlineJournalInfo": {"Country": "Germany", "MedlineTA": "Plant Cell Rep", "NlmUniqueID": "9880970", "ISSNLinking": "0721-7714"}, "ChemicalList": [{"RegistryNumber": "0", "NameOfSubstance": "DNA, Chloroplast"}], "MeshHeadingList": [{"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Amplified Fragment Length Polymorphism Analysis"}, {"QualifierName": ["cytology", "genetics"], "DescriptorName": "Brassica napus"}, {"QualifierName": ["genetics"], "DescriptorName": "Chimera"}, {"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Chromosomes, Plant"}, {"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Cytogenetic Analysis"}, {"QualifierName": ["genetics"], "DescriptorName": "DNA, Chloroplast"}, {"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Fertility"}, {"QualifierNa